statement.p:
A function f(x) defined on the whole real number line satisfies the following conditions
f(0)=0\qquad f(2)=2\qquad \lim_{x\rightarrow+\infty}f(x)=0\qquad f'(x)=K(2x-x^2)e^{-x}
for some positive constant K. (Read carefully: you are given the derivative of f(x), not f(x) itself.)

